f=Engineering/aegis/marketplace/threat-model/schema.md ┬╖ h1:THREAT_MODEL.md schema=**Re-read note:** you need file mid-session Read tool reports "file unchanged", prior result evicted context; reload `cat .claude/skills/threat-model/schema.md` Bash. `/threat-model interview` `/threat-model bootstrap` write file `<target-dir>/THREAT_MODEL.md`. format markdown humans read edit it, section headings, table columns, enum values below contract: keep headings column order exactly shown downstream tooling parse them regex. ┬╖ h3:1. System context=One three paragraphs prose: what system is, what does, who uses it, runs. table. answer "what working on?". ┬╖ h3:2. Assets=Markdown table. One row thing worth protecting. ┬╖ h3:2. Assets=\| asset \| description \| sensitivity \| ┬╖ h3:2. Assets=\|---\|---\|---\| ┬╖ h3:2. Assets=`sensitivity` {`low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical`}. ┬╖ h3:Entry points trust boundaries=Markdown table. One row place untrusted input enters system privilege level changes. ┬╖ h3:Entry points trust boundaries=\| entry_point \| description \| trust_boundary \| reachable_assets \| ┬╖ h3:Entry points trust boundaries=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| ┬╖ h3:Entry points trust boundaries=`trust_boundary` free text naming crossing (e.g. "untrusted file process memory", "unauth network authenticated session"). `reachable_assets` comma-separated list asset names section ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=Markdown table. **This threat model proper.** One row actor-wants-outcome pair, abstraction level survives patch. ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=\| id \| threat \| actor \| surface \| asset \| impact \| likelihood \| status \| controls \| evidence \| ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`id`: `T1`, `T2`, Stable across edits; renumber rows ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=removed. ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`threat`: One sentence, active voice, names outcome. "Remote code ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=execution untrusted media parsing", "buffer overflow dr_wav". ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`actor` {`remote_unauth`, `remote_auth`, `adjacent_network`, ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`local_user`, `local_admin`, `supply_chain`, `insider`}. ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`surface`: Which entry point(s) section threat traverses., `asset`: Which asset(s) section threat compromises., `impact` {`low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical`, `existential`}., `likelihood` {`very_rare`, `rare`, `possible`, `likely`, ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`almost_certain`}. ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`status` {`unmitigated`, `partially_mitigated`, `mitigated`, ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`risk_accepted`}. ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=`controls`: Current mitigations, `none`., `evidence`: CVE IDs, issue links, pentest finding IDs, git commit ┬╖ h3:4. Threats=hashes **instantiate** threat. empty. **Evidence raises likelihood; threat.** Sort table (impact, likelihood) descending top rows priorities. ┬╖ h3:5. Deprioritized=Markdown table. Threats considered explicitly parked. ┬╖ h3:5. Deprioritized=\| threat \| reason \| ┬╖ h3:5. Deprioritized=\|---\|---\| ┬╖ h3:5. Deprioritized=Common reasons: out scope, actor threat model, asset present, risk accepted owner. ┬╖ h3:6. Open questions=Bullet list. Things mode determine. `bootstrap` questions human owner; `interview` claims owner made verifiable code. ┬╖ h3:7. Provenance=`- mode: interview \| bootstrap \| bootstrap-then-interview \┬╖ - date: YYYY-MM-DD \┬╖ - target: <path or repo url @ commit> \┬╖ - inputs: <design doc path \| --vulns path \| "none"> \┬╖ - owner: <name, for interview> \| <unset, for bootstrap>` ┬╖ h3:8. Recommended mitigations=`\| mitigation \| threat_ids \| closes_class \| effort \| \┬╖ \|---\|---\|---\|---\|` ┬╖ h3:8. Recommended mitigations=Optional, additive: older `THREAT_MODEL.md` files omit section, consumers tolerate absence. row **one class-level control**, per-finding patch: mitigation closes materially shrinks entire threat cluster regardless which instance found next. ┬╖ h3:8. Recommended mitigations=`mitigation`: imperative, one line (e.g., "sandbox decoder process", ┬╖ h3:8. Recommended mitigations="parameterized queries everywhere", "drop pickle json", "enable CSP default-src 'self'", "size-cap length fields before allocation"). ┬╖ h3:8. Recommended mitigations=`threat_ids`: comma-separated section ids (e.g., `T1,T3`) mitigation covers., `closes_class`: `yes` \| `partial`., `effort`: `S` `M` `L`. ┬╖ h2:Example (excerpt)=`## 4. Threats \┬╖  \┬╖ \| id \| threat \| actor \| surface \| asset \| impact \| likelihood \| status \| controls \| evidence \| \┬╖ \|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| \┬╖ \| T1 \| Memory corruption leading to RCE via untrusted audio file parsing \| remote_unauth \| dr_wav/dr_flac decoders \| host process integrity \| critical \| likely \| unmitigated \| none \| CVE-2026-29022, CVE-2025-14369 \|` ┬╖ h2:Example (excerpt)=stays model after CVEs patched: attackers still send malformed audio files. CVEs evidence surface fertile, threat itself.